icly cautioned its former chief executive e hunter harrison on friday against participating in the hedge fund manager william a ackman’s plan to put him in charge of running the canadian pacific railway saying that would violate his employment contract mr harrison is widely credited with turning canadian national into one of north america’s most costefficient railways but the directors of canadian pacific have rejected mr ackman’s proposal to have him lead a similar transformation at that railroad which lags behind canadian national in efficiency earlier this week mr ackman whose firm pershing square capital management is the largest shareholder in canadian pacific said he was planning a proxy battle to replace the company’s board in order to make mr harrison the railroad’s chief executive canadian national however does not appear interested in seeing mr harrison improve the fortunes of its rival “as part of his employment contract with cn mr harrison agreed upon retirement as president and chief executive officer on dec   to be bound by a broad range of confidentiality and multiyear noncompetition and nonsolicitation provisions” canadian national said in an email statement “cn has asked mr harrison to respect his commitments to cn and to reconsider his expressed interest in a position at canadian pacific” the montrealbased railroad said “cn has also put william a ackman of pershing square capital management lp on notice to cease any efforts to induce breaches of mr harrison’s contractual obligations to cn” mr harrison’s blanket noncompete agreement with canadian national expired at the end of  but canadian national said in an earlier statement that his retirement and pension arrangements separately prohibited him from competing against the company or trying to hire its employees until the end of  daniel ackerbloomberg newsthe hedge manager william a ackman mr ackman said monday that mr harrison was “excited by the opportunity” of running a railway again mr harrison expressed similar sentiments in an interview with the globe and mail of toronto earlier this week the two men met on friday and mr ackman said in an interview that mr harrison was still interested in becoming the chief executive of canadian pacific despite the warning from canadian national mr ackman acknowledged that if he was successful in changing chief executives mr harrison would lose his canadian national pension and require compensation from canadian pacific but he characterized the cost of that arrangement as “not material” to canadian pacific he also said friday that canadian national’s warning was an endorsement of mr harrison’s skills “this confirms to me that he’s the best man for this job” mr ackman said whats next loading previous post lead rajaratnam prosecutor to join dechert next post dealbook’s week in review advertisement e hunter harrison  wikipedia e hunter harrison from wikipedia the free encyclopedia jump to navigation search ewing hunter harrison born november   is a railway executive who served as the ceo of illinois central railroad ic canadian national railway cn and canadian pacific railway cpr and now serves as ceo of csx biographyedit born in memphis tennessee in  harrison began his railroad career in  while attending memphis state university when he worked as a carmanoiler for the st louissan francisco railway frisco harrison was later promoted to railroad operator with frisco and later with burlington northern railroad bn following that companys acquisition of frisco in  harrison was consistently promoted at bn eventually being appointed vicepresident  transportation as well as vicepresident  service design harrison in  left the bn and secured a job with the executive team at the illinois central railroad ic first as vicepresident and chief operating officer culminating with his appointment as president and chief executive officer from  to  following the acquisition of ic by canadian national railway cn in  harrison was appointed vicepresident and chief operating officer by cn upon the retirement of paul tellier he was appointed president and chief executive officer of cn on january   serving in that position until his retirement on december  citation needed during his time at cn harrison was named railroader of the year for  by industry trade journal railway age as well as ceo of the year for  by the globe and mails report on business on april   cn announced the companys plan for succession in harrisons position by appointing claude mongeau as his successor effective january   following his service at cn harrison retired to his estate in connecticut where he raises and trains horses for show jumping bound by a noncompetition clause with cn harrison maintained a low profile serving as a director for the belt railway of chicago as well as dynegy holdings llccitation needed in fall  harrison was approached by the hedge fund pershing square capital management led by activist investor bill ackman who was undertaking a proxy battle with the board of directors of canadian pacific railway cpr ackman had offered at that time to appoint harrison as president and chief executive officer of cpr should his proxy battle in spring  be successful which would necessarily result in the termination of fred green as president and ceo ackman was ultimately successful in the proxy battle at the cprs annual shareholder meeting on may   on june   harrison was appointed president and ceo of canadian pacific railway the canadian national railway co halted nearly million in benefits to be paid to harrison after launching a lawsuit alleging he may have breached or intends to breach several confidentiality agreements with the railway dating back to his retirement in  in the suit cns board of directors said it had grounds to believe harrison may have violated his commitments to cn as part of push by activist shareholder william ackman and his new yorkbased hedge fund pershing capital management llc to see harrison replace fred green as ceo of rival canadian pacific railway ltd on january   hunter harrison abruptly resigned as ceo of canadian pacific railway ltd instead he joined paul hilal in involving himself in the management of csx corp a us competitor on march   harrison was named ceo of csx referencesedit  cp’s hunter harrison ‘there is a new sheriff in town’ the globe and mail retrieved  december    investor  canadian national railway co archived from the original on may   retrieved november     e hunter harrison cbrca retrieved november     cn board of directors approves oneyear contract extension for company’s president and chief executive officer press release canadian national railway november   retrieved december     ‘high probability’ excnr head would take cp helm financial post accessed april    as harrison takes cp’s top job ackmans coup is complete the globe and mail accessed april    cn suspends hunter harrisons pension payments the globe and mail  retrieved    benoit david ziobro paul mcnish jacquie january   csx investors cheered by former rail rival’s sudden switch new york the wall street journal retrieved january     allaire yvan dauphin francois january   someone just hired hunter harrison for  million — and there’s an excellent reason why toronto financial post retrieved january     stephens bill march   hunter harrison named ceo at csx transportation trainscom waukesha wisconsin usa retrieved march    preceded by edward moyers president of illinois central railroad  –  purchase by canadian national railway preceded by mike haverty atsf kcs railroader of the year  succeeded by richard k davidson up preceded by paul tellier president of canadian national railway  –  succeeded by claude mongeau preceded by fred green president  ceo of canadian pacific  –  succeeded by keith creel retrieved from httpsenwikipediaorgwindexphptitleehunterharrisonoldid categories  birthsliving peoplebusinesspeople from tennesseecanadian pacific railway executivescanadian national rail