kipedia e hunter harrison from wikipedia the free encyclopedia jump to navigation search ewing hunter harrison born november   is a railway executive who served as the ceo of illinois central railroad ic canadian national railway cn and canadian pacific railway cpr and now serves as ceo of csx biographyedit born in memphis tennessee in  harrison began his railroad career in  while attending memphis state university when he worked as a carmanoiler for the st louissan francisco railway frisco harrison was later promoted to railroad operator with frisco and later with burlington northern railroad bn following that companys acquisition of frisco in  harrison was consistently promoted at bn eventually being appointed vicepresident  transportation as well as vicepresident  service design harrison in  left the bn and secured a job with the executive team at the illinois central railroad ic first as vicepresident and chief operating officer culminating with his appointment as president and chief executive officer from  to  following the acquisition of ic by canadian national railway cn in  harrison was appointed vicepresident and chief operating officer by cn upon the retirement of paul tellier he was appointed president and chief executive officer of cn on january   serving in that position until his retirement on december  citation needed during his time at cn harrison was named railroader of the year for  by industry trade journal railway age as well as ceo of the year for  by the globe and mails report on business on april   cn announced the companys plan for succession in harrisons position by appointing claude mongeau as his successor effective january   following his service at cn harrison retired to his estate in connecticut where he raises and trains horses for show jumping bound by a noncompetition clause with cn harrison maintained a low profile serving as a director for the belt railway of chicago as well as dynegy holdings llccitation needed in fall  harrison was approached by the hedge fund pershing square capital management led by activist investor bill ackman who was undertaking a proxy battle with the board of directors of canadian pacific railway cpr ackman had offered at that time to appoint harrison as president and chief executive officer of cpr should his proxy battle in spring  be successful which would necessarily result in the termination of fred green as president and ceo ackman was ultimately successful in the proxy battle at the cprs annual shareholder meeting on may   on june   harrison was appointed president and ceo of canadian pacific railway the canadian national railway co halted nearly million in benefits to be paid to harrison after launching a lawsuit alleging he may have breached or intends to breach several confidentiality agreements with the railway dating back to his retirement in  in the suit cns board of directors said it had grounds to believe harrison may have violated his commitments to cn as part of push by activist shareholder william ackman and his new yorkbased hedge fund pershing capital management llc to see harrison replace fred green as ceo of rival canadian pacific railway ltd on january   hunter harrison abruptly resigned as ceo of canadian pacific railway ltd instead he joined paul hilal in involving himself in the management of csx corp a us competitor on march   harrison was named ceo of csx referencesedit  cp’s hunter harrison ‘there is a new sheriff in town’ the globe and mail retrieved  december    investor  canadian national railway co archived from the original on may   retrieved november     e hunter harrison cbrca retrieved november     cn board of directors approves oneyear contract extension for company’s president and chief executive officer press release canadian national railway november   retrieved december     ‘high probability’ excnr head would take cp helm financial post accessed april    as harrison takes cp’s top job ackmans coup is complete the globe and mai